sec.p:
Practical test application: All n values from the k-independent samples are rank-ordered from the lowest (rank 1) to the highest. The sum of the ranks in the j-th group ($j=1,2,\ldots , k$) is marked Rj as shown in Eqs. (7) and (8) as follows.
(7)\begin{equation}\text{Checking}\colon R_{1}+R_{2}+\cdots +R_{k}=\frac{n\left(n+1\right)}{2}\end{equation}
(8)\begin{equation}Q=\frac{1}{12(n(n+1))}\sum \nolimits _{i=1}^{k}\,\left(\frac{R_{i}^{2}}{n_{i}}\right)-3(n+1)\end{equation}
